Preconditions:
- The input array `arr` is not null.
- The length of the input array `arr` is at least 1 and at most 10^5.
- Each element in the input array `arr` is an integer between -10^4 and 10^4.

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer representing the maximum sum of a non-empty subarray with at most one element deletion.
- The subarray chosen has at least one element remaining after the deletion.
- The sum of the remaining elements in the subarray is the maximum possible.